name: Nungnung Waterfall Carpark
address: Pelaga, Petang, Badung Regency, Bali 80353, Indonesia
review 1: The way down and up may be exhausting, but it's definitely worth it. There were only a few people there, which made the experience even more enjoyable. Highly recommended if you're in the area.
review 2: A stunning, powerful, waterfall. 42k entry cost (for 2 people and 1 bike). Steep set of stairs down to the waterfall (which make the climb back up a bit of a physical challenge). Once you're down at the waterfall it's incredible. The water is cool and the spray is monumental.
review 3: 10/10 waterfall, beautiful, gigantic powerful, amazing nature and very chill temperature down there.
review 4:
Amazing waterfall, the best I have ever seen. The energy & the vibes seeing it in front of u is incredible. I dont think any picture or video can transfer that feeling. The way up is quite hard üòÇ

We loved it, will come back if possible
review 5:
A popular place among tourists. I had to wait 40 minutes to take a photo without people.

The waterfall is beautiful and powerful, especially if you come close to it. There are good, but long steps leading to the place. I recommend combining a visit to this waterfall with other places.
